---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Roadmap: Asteris Commerce cross-product release timeline"
  description="Cross-product roadmap for Asteris for WooCommerce, Asteris for WordPress, and Asteris Cart. v1.0 ship status, v1.1+ planned modules, research-needed candidates. Honest about what's built vs what's banked."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Roadmap</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Cross-product release timeline across all three Asteris plugins. Honest about what's shipped, what's banked, and what's still under research. Dates are intentionally absent: see the <a href="https://asterisforwoocommerce.com/lifetime/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">no-hard-dates rule</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="body">
    <div class="container">

      <div class="grid">
        <!-- Asteris for WooCommerce row -->
        <div class="prod-col prod-col--wc">
          <div class="prod-eyebrow">★ Asteris for WooCommerce</div>
          <h2>WC roadmap</h2>

          <h3 class="phase">v1.0: shipped</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="ok">✓</span> 20 modules built and shipped at plugin v1.9.20</li>
            <li><span class="ok">✓</span> AI Suite · SEO · PDF Invoices · Variation Swatches · Wishlist · Quote / Enquiry · Back in Stock · Side Cart · Sequential Order Numbers · Product Filtering · Min/Max Quantity · Asteris Links · Trust Badges · Free Shipping Bar · Stock Urgency · Delivery Timeline · Feature Labels · Product Badges · Analytics · Asteris Coupons</li>
            <li><span class="ok">✓</span> 6 of those modules in Asteris Free (WordPress.org)</li>
            <li><span class="ok">✓</span> HPOS-verified · Block Cart compatible · 6-theme tested</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="phase">v1.1: first post-launch release</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Asteris Cookie Consent</strong> — GDPR / ePrivacy / CCPA / LGPD-compliant banner with real script-blocking. Hero feature of v1.1 release. Replaces CookieYes / Cookiebot / Iubenda ($79–$348/yr SaaS each).</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> WordPress Multisite support</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> WP-CLI commands (agency-scale operations)</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> Customer self-service /account portal (licence management, downloads, invoices)</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> Module 20 (Coupons) deferred features: AI-generated coupon copy, subscription-aware rules, stacking</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="phase">v1.2: second release</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> <strong>Asteris Checkout Customizer</strong> — field-level checkout customisation (add/remove/reorder fields, conditional logic, custom thank-you pages). Research-needed.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="phase">Research-needed (v1.2+)</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> <strong>Asteris Social Proof</strong> — recent-purchase / activity notifications. NotificationX / TrustPulse replacement. Honest-data-only positioning.</li>
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> <strong>Asteris Payment Icons</strong> — trust-signal payment-method icons at checkout / footer / product page</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="phase">v2+: under consideration</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> <strong>Asteris Funnel Builder</strong> — full CartFlows / FunnelKit replacement (multi-step funnel pages, one-click upsells, order bumps, A/B testing). EXPLICITLY DEFERRED with documented blocking concerns; revisit when there's evidence of customer demand and team capacity.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Asteris for WordPress row -->
        <div class="prod-col prod-col--wp">
          <div class="prod-eyebrow">★ Asteris for WordPress</div>
          <h2>WP roadmap</h2>

          <h3 class="phase">v1.0: building (sequential ship)</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="ok">✓</span> Module Quality Protocol locked: every module closes Tier 1 + Tier 2 gap analysis before the next module starts</li>
            <li><span class="building">●</span> <strong>Security + Login + 2FA</strong> — flagship wedge module. Built quality-first vs Wordfence Premium.</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>SEO + AI</strong> — full SEO toolkit with AI-written meta. Shared with WC product.</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Backups + Migration</strong> — scheduled + offsite + one-click restore.</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>SMTP + Email Logs</strong> — major provider integrations + log table + deliverability alerts.</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> 7 more modules planned for v1.0: see asterisforwordpress.com for the full list</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="phase">v1.1+: banked</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> WordPress Multisite support</li>
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> Performance + Image Optimisation</li>
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> Activity Log</li>
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> Code Snippets</li>
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> Accessibility tooling</li>
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> Forms</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="phase">v1.5+: deferred</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> Custom Fields + Post Types (deferred past Feb 2027 ACF / SCF trial period)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- Asteris Cart row -->
        <div class="prod-col prod-col--cart">
          <div class="prod-eyebrow">★ Asteris Cart</div>
          <h2>Cart roadmap</h2>

          <h3 class="phase">v1.0: alpha (pre-launch)</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="ok">✓</span> 21 modules built and wired at plugin v1.0.0-alpha.9</li>
            <li><span class="ok">✓</span> Side Cart · Free Shipping Bar · Cart Page · Floating Button · Add-to-Cart Popup · Mobile Sticky Bar · Empty Cart · Shipping Calculator · Coupon URL · Sticky Checkout Button · Pixel Bridge · Trust Badges · Login · Thank-You Page · Express Checkout · GDPR Consent · Quote Mode · Multi-Step · Urgency Timer · Field Editor · Safe Mode</li>
            <li><span class="ok">✓</span> HPOS code-verified · Block Cart compatible · Classic-hooks-first</li>
            <li><span class="building">●</span> End-to-end QA on real store + cross-theme verification (in progress)</li>
            <li><span class="building">●</span> Public launch: Founder Hundred → open launch: velocity-decided window</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="phase">v1.1: first post-launch release</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Recovery + Bot Filter</strong> — abandoned-cart capture with IP fingerprinting, session validation, rate limiting. The flagship v1.1 wedge: every competitor's recovery metric is bot-poisoned.</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Sequence Runner</strong> — email recovery drips on WP Mail. Resend/Postmark integrations land later.</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Exit-Intent Popup</strong> — last-chance offer before tab close, integrated with Recovery for opt-in capture.</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Customer Portal</strong> — self-service licence management, downloads, invoices (no need to email support).</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Multisite Support</strong> — network-activated mode for agency Multisite installs.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="phase">v1.2: upsell flow</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Order Bumps</strong> — pre-purchase upsell offers in the checkout summary (code already drafted, ships full in v1.2).</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Post-Purchase Upsells</strong> — one-click acceptance on the thank-you page using the original gateway token.</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Downsells</strong> — alternate offer when an upsell is declined.</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Coupon Bar</strong> — site-wide auto-applying promo bar with eligibility rules.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="phase">v1.3: UX polish</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Address Autocomplete</strong> — pluggable Google / Mapbox / Loqate / OS Places backends. Merchant brings their own key: no Asteris-proxied billing.</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Express Checkout v2</strong> — gateway-agnostic Payment Request API wrapper, surfaces Stripe + WooPayments + Square + Mollie native PRBs.</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>WP-CLI Suite</strong> — agency-scale <code>wp asteris-cart</code> commands for bulk activation, module toggle, status export.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="phase">v1.4: analytics + growth (agency-tier)</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>A/B Testing</strong> — per-module variant testing with statistical significance gates. Surfaces results in admin.</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Analytics Dashboard</strong> — unified revenue view: which modules drove which conversions, attribution surviving custom URLs.</li>
            <li><span class="planned">●</span> <strong>Cohort Reports</strong> — recovery cohort survival curves, urgency-timer effect on AOV, GDPR opt-in rates by region.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="phase">v1.5+: research-needed</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> <strong>AI Recovery Timing</strong> — optimal send-time per cohort. Honest-data-only: no fake ML claims, must beat fixed-window baseline by N% in real tests.</li>
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> <strong>SMS Recovery</strong> — Twilio / MessageBird send paths. Carrier compliance per market.</li>
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> <strong>Block Checkout Mode</strong> — full Asteris UX on WC's Block Checkout once WC core ships custom-step support. Currently classic-hooks-only by design.</li>
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> <strong>Agentic Hooks</strong> — MCP-style endpoints for AI assistants to manage cart/checkout config. Spec-pending.</li>
          </ul>

          <h3 class="phase">v2+: under consideration</h3>
          <ul class="mod-list">
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> <strong>Funnel Canvas</strong> — visual multi-page funnel builder (the one feature CartFlows beats us on today). EXPLICITLY DEFERRED: only revisit when customer demand is documented and team capacity allows.</li>
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> <strong>Agency Plus Tier</strong>:$799+ white-label option. Only ships if real demand surfaces (no white-label in v1.0–v1.5).</li>
            <li><span class="research">◯</span> <strong>Multi-currency Switcher</strong> — if WC core doesn't ship it first. Currently under WC Roadmap consideration.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="legend">
        <span><span class="ok">✓</span> shipped</span>
        <span><span class="building">●</span> in active build</span>
        <span><span class="planned">●</span> planned + scoped</span>
        <span><span class="research">◯</span> research-needed before scoping</span>
      </div>

      <div class="rules">
        <h2>Roadmap rules</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>No hard dates published.</strong> Stage transitions are velocity-decided. Publishing a date and missing it is worse than not publishing one.</li>
          <li><strong>Module Quality Protocol is non-negotiable.</strong> Tier 1 + Tier 2 features ship together. No "decoration tier" modules.</li>
          <li><strong>Shared modules built once.</strong> SEO + AI, Analytics, Links, AI library are vendored into both plugins. Same code, no plugin-to-plugin dependency.</li>
          <li><strong>Research-needed = not yet scoped.</strong> An item being on the roadmap doesn't mean it will ship. Each research-needed module gets a deep-research workflow + Sovereign sign-off before it enters the build queue.</li>
          <li><strong>Customer feedback weights priority.</strong> Post-launch, the highest-feedback items move up. The roadmap above is the pre-launch best-guess.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero { padding: 80px 0 40px; }
  h1 {
    font-size: 64px;
    line-height: 1;
    letter-spacing: -2px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .lead {
    font-size: 22px;
    color: var(--c-muted);
    max-width: 720px;
  }
  .lead a { color: var(--c-orange); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  @media (max-width: 700px) { h1 { font-size: 40px; } }

  .body { padding: 40px 0 80px; }
  .grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: 32px;
  }

  .prod-col {
    background: var(--c-white);
    border: 2px solid var(--c-black);
    border-top: 6px solid var(--prod-accent, var(--c-orange));
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    padding: 36px 40px;
  }
  .prod-col--wc   { --prod-accent: #FF5B3F; }
  .prod-col--wp   { --prod-accent: #3D5AFE; }
  .prod-col--cart { --prod-accent: #00C853; }
  .prod-eyebrow {
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--prod-accent, var(--c-orange));
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }
  .prod-col h2 {
    font-size: 30px;
    margin-bottom: 24px;
  }
  .phase {
    font-size: 17px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    color: var(--c-muted);
    margin: 28px 0 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .mod-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }
  .mod-list li {
    font-size: 22px;
    line-height: 1.55;
    padding: 10px 0;
    color: #333;
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }
  .mod-list li strong { color: var(--c-black); }
  .ok { color: var(--c-orange); font-weight: 900; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .building { color: var(--c-orange); font-weight: 900; flex-shrink: 0; }
  .planned { color: var(--c-muted); flex-shrink: 0; }
  .research { color: var(--c-faint); flex-shrink: 0; }

  .legend {
    margin: 48px 0 32px;
    display: flex;
    gap: 24px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    font-size: 14px;
    color: var(--c-muted);
  }
  .legend span span {
    margin-right: 6px;
  }

  .rules {
    background: var(--c-black);
    color: #cccccc;
    padding: 48px;
    border-radius: var(--r-lg);
    margin-top: 32px;
  }
  .rules h2 { color: var(--c-white); font-size: 26px; margin-bottom: 16px; }
  .rules ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
  .rules ul li { padding: 12px 0; font-size: 22px; line-height: 1.55; }
  .rules ul li strong { color: var(--c-white); }
</style>
